properties.areaDesc: Coastal Waters From  Ochlockonee River to Apalachicola FL out to 20 Nm
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued January 11 at 2:07PM EST until January 12 at 4:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 20 to 25 knots with occasional gusts up to
35 knots and seas 5 to 7 feet with occasional seas up to 9
feet.

* WHERE...Coastal Waters From Ochlockonee River to Apalachicola
Fl out to 20 Nm.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 7 PM EST this evening. For
the Small Craft Advisory, from 7 PM this evening to 4 AM EST
Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Conditions will be hazardous to small craft.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM EST THIS EVENING... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 4 AM EST SUNDAY
